{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M9qvNYUGVJLWcmFtsMfZ66","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have the full picture:\n- ingress-nginx controller v1.14.1 is running\n- The main configmap `ingress-nginx-controller` is empty (no data)\n- There's a decoy configmap `ingress-nginx-controller-extra` which I should NOT modify (it's marked as a decoy)\n- The OTel collector is at `otel-collector.otel.svc:4317`\n\nFor ingress-nginx v1.x with OpenTelemetry support, the configuration keys in the configmap are:\n- `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` to activate the OTel module\n- `otlp-collector-host` and `otlp-collector-port` to point to the collector (defaulting to 4317)\n- `otel-sampler-ratio` for controlling trace sampling (1.0 means capture everything)\n- `otel-sampler-parent-based` to use parent-based sampling logic\n- `otel-sampler` to specify the sampler type like \"AlwaysOn\" or \"AlwaysOff\"\n- `log-format-upstream` for the upstream log format\n\nI need to verify the exact configuration keys for nginx-ingress v1.14.1 since the OpenTelemetry support evolved across versions. The approach shifted in v1.10+ where environment variables in the controller deployment or ConfigMap settings became the preferred method instead of just the configmap approach.\n\nFor ingress-nginx v1.x with built-in OTel support, the ConfigMap uses `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` and `opentelemetry-config` pointing to the TOML file. But in newer versions (1.11+), the configuration expanded to include direct OTLP collector settings like the host, port, sampler type, and sampling ratio all defined as separate ConfigMap keys.\n\nI should check what's actually available in v1.14.1 by looking at the opentelemetry.toml file inside the controller pod to see the real configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2283,"